added.title: Wishbone
added.description: The Titans make wishes on a wishbone, but when it's broken, they must travel to Gobble-Gobble Land to set things right.

added.title: A Doom Patrol Thanksgiving
added.description: Beast Boy returns home for Thanksgiving and the Doom Patrol enter a float in the town's parade. / The Doom Patrol finds old home movies about themselves that The Chief had hidden.

added.title: The Scoop
added.description: The Titans find it odd when Starfire becomes friends with an ice cream scoop.

added.title: Chicken in the Cradle
added.description: Beast Boy neglects his responsibilities, leaving the other Titans to raise his baby chick.

added.title: Thanksgetting
added.description: It's Thanksgiving but the Titans are sick of the normal traditions so they create their own.

added.title: Croissant
added.description: A giant cocoon mysteriously appears in the Titans' living room, and no one can find Beast Boy.

added.title: Black Friday
added.description: Starfire is visited by three ghosts and shown the true meaning of Black Friday.

added.title: Vegetables
added.description: The Titans try vegetarianism, but learn that not everyone is cut out for that lifestyle.

added.title: Thanksgiving
added.description: When Raven's father Trigon shows up for Thanksgiving dinner, Robin's seating plan isn't the only thing that gets ruined.

added.title: Legendary Sandwich
added.description: The team goes on a series of epic quests in order to create the world's perfect sandwich.

added.title: Meatball Party
added.description: Raven eats a bad meatball that causes tentacles to spring from her teeth and devour the other Titans.

added.title: The Potato
added.description: When Darwin has lunch with Idaho, he decides to stop eating potatoes in solidarity with his brotato. However, he finds his obsession with his favourite food harder to kick than he ever imagined so Gumball decides to help his friend curb his carb cravings.

added.title: The Boss
added.description: Gumball and Darwin help Rocky land an office job so that his dad, Mr. Robinson, will be proud of him. After a health scare the kids decide to reunite Mr Robinson with his son. Mr Robinson has always seen Rocky as a disappointment so when Gumball and Darwin help him land a corporate job at Chanax, he is thrilled. However the Chanax corporation is not quite what it seems. Can Gumball and Darwin rescue Rocky before he becomes a corporate drone for all eternity . . .

added.title: The Pizza
added.description: The Wattersons have had a bad day, but it turns out Larry has too and it's about to get worse . . . for everyone! The Wattersons complain about their day and order a pizza from Larry. When they call to complain about their late pizza it's the final straw for Larry and he quits all of his jobs. Elmore's fragile commercial structure collapses and the citizens revert to a more primitive apocalyptic state.

added.title: The Friend
added.description: Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who turns out to be all too real. Anais throws a party but no-one shows up as she has no friends or social skills. Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who, much to all their surprise, appears in front of them. Gumball and Darwin teach Anais and her new friend how to become friends, but soon realise that he might not be so imaginary after all...

added.title: The Egg
added.description: To impress the mother of Anais' playdate, Nicole forces her family to get classy. Nicole arranges a playdate for Anais with the son of a classy lady she met at the supermarket. She hopes that socializing with the right sort of people will help her children climb Elmore's social ladder. The Wattersons try to impress, but ultimately cannot help revealing their true natures. The grown-ups become convinced they want nothing more to do with each other, just as Anais and her playdate discover how much they have in common.

added.title: The Recipe
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the secret behind Anton's immortality. Anton's little toasty body disintegrates during a swim class. When Gumball and Darwin see Anton the next day, as good as new, they set out to discover his secret. It turns out that his parents use a special formula to bake new Antons when necessary. So the kids test it out at home and end up baking a clone army whose leader - Ant-one - wants to destroy Anton and take over the world.

added.title: The Shell
added.description: Gumball inadvertently cracks open Penny's shell and discovers who she really is inside . . . While performing a school play, Gumball is so nervous about kissing Penny that he accidentally headbutts her and cracks open her shell. They discover that under Penny's shell is an emotional shape-shifting inner self. Penny's father is determined for Penny to keep it hidden but Gumball encourages her to show the world who, or what, she really is . . .

added.title: The Question
added.description: Gumball and Darwin seek the answer to the biggest question of all: what is the meaning of life? They need to understand the point of their lives, so resolve to seek advice from everyone in Elmore. They ask people, animals and even planets but their answer comes from an unexpected source.

added.title: The Saint
added.description: Gumball doesn't believe anyone could really be as nice as Alan and sets out to find his breaking point. Alan is so good-natured that Gumball feels compelled to make him lose his temper. Despite turning the whole school against him, destroying his relationship with Carmen and even selling his parents, Alan remains understanding and happy. Defeated, Gumball and Darwin decide to adopt Alan's positive attitude to see if they can be more like Alan.Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who turns out to be all too real. Anais throws a party but no-one shows up as she has no friends or social skills. Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who, much to all their surprise, appears in front of them. Gumball and Darwin teach Anais and her new friend how to become friends but realize he might not be so imaginary after all.

added.title: The Fridge
added.description: When Mom discovers Gumball has no ambition she is determined to turn him into a winner.

added.title: The Banana
added.description: Darwin lends his pen to Banana Joe but, when it comes back chewed, Gumball's thoughts turn to revenge.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are unwitting accomplices in a gas station robbery.

added.title: The Picnic
added.description: Gumball and Darwin barely survive a school picnic in the Forest of Doom

added.title: The Ape
added.description: Ms Simian sets out to "befriend" Gumball in order to win a Favourite Teacher Award.

added.title: The Microwave
added.description: Gumball and Darwin accidentally create a loveable monster that eats their family.

added.title: Fall Anthology
added.description: In an attempt to finish a school project, Craig remembers some of his favorite Fall moments.

added.title: Afterschool Snackdown
added.description: Craig enters a food competition in the Creek but worries he may be out of his league.

added.title: Sour Candy Trials
added.description: Craig goes on a mind-bending journey as he tries to eat the most sour candy in the Creek!

added.title: Turning the Tables
added.description: Craig dines at the restaurant where his older brother works and orders up a plate of REVENGE... and lots of breadsticks.

added.title: Craig and the Kid's Table
added.description: It's a Williams Family Thanksgiving, which means it's time to reunite The Kid's Table! But when Bernard accidentally destroys dessert, Craig uses the power of the Kids Table to help save his brother from certain grounding.

added.title: Sugar Smugglers
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP become smugglers to sneak candy to kids in need.

added.title: Tea Timer's Ball
added.description: The Tea Timers throw a dance and invite everyone in the Creek. Craig believes it's solely to prank him, while Kelsey deals with an unwanted admirer.

added.title: Itch to Explore
added.description: Craig's quest to map the entire Creek takes him and his friends into the treacherous Poison Ivy Grove.

added.title: You're It
added.description: A vicious game of tag wreaks havoc on the Creek, claiming Kelsey as the next it.

added.title: Jessica Goes to the Creek
added.description: When Craig and Jessica are locked out of the house, Craig has no choice but to bring his little sister to the Creek.

added.title: The Final Book
added.description: The last book of Kelsey's favorite fantasy series goes missing from the library, so Craig decides to help her solve the mystery of who took it.

added.title: Too Many Treasures
added.description: Hoping to fix their fort, Craig enlists the 10 Speeds to give them a ride to the legendary Junk Pile.

added.title: Escape from Family Dinner
added.description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

added.title: The Takeout Mission
added.description: Kelsey leads her friends on the most important quest ever, picking up takeout for dinner.

added.title: Dinner at the Creek
added.description: Bernard is left in charge for the evening, so Craig sets out to find his own dinner at the creek.

added.title: Crowbar Jones: Origins
added.description: Grizz pitches his Crowbar Jones prequel film to Nom Nom, hoping Nom Nom will agree to appear in the movie.

added.title: Hot Sauce
added.description: A quest for their favorite hot sauce causes the Bears to get involved with a sting operation.

added.title: Mom App
added.description: Hoping to finally get the mom-experience, the Bears use an app that'll bring a mom right to their door.

added.title: The Limo
added.description: To help distract Panda from his girl problems, Grizz and Ice Bear treat him to a ride in a limo.

added.title: More Everyone's Tube
added.description: Through another video browsing session online, we get more videos uploaded by the Bears and their friends.

added.title: Money Man
added.description: The Bears help Chloe present her project for a college science contest. But Chloe's rival makes things difficult.

added.title: Rescue Ranger
added.description: Tabes helps the Bears rescue Charlie after he gets captured by a villainous game hunter.

added.title: El Oso
added.description: In a flashback to long ago, Charlie has an adventure in the Mexican desert.

added.title: Escandalosos
added.description: The Baby Bears enter a Mexican wrestling tournament.

added.title: Pizza Band
added.description: The Bears get pizza at Papa Bear's Pizza Cave and wind up replacing the place's animatronic band. They're such a hit that they go on tour!

added.title: Adopted
added.description: The Baby Bears get adopted by an eccentric millionaire and get to live in his mansion.

added.title: Wingmen
added.description: In order to get some sleep, the Bears help an annoying bird find a new mate.

added.title: Braces
added.description: When the Bears go to the dentist, Panda gets braces. But, Panda finds out his braces grant him super abilities and the power goes to his head.

added.title: Imaginary Friend
added.description: The Baby Bears invent an imaginary friend, but the trouble he causes is all too real.

added.title: The Mall
added.description: The Bears go the mall and encounter their human counterparts.

added.title: Say Uncle
added.description: A long lost relative of Steven's comes to town to aid him in unlocking the power of his mother's Gem!

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Shirt Club
added.description: Steven and Buck Dewey make t-shirts together.

added.title: Love Letters
added.description: Steven and Connie help Jamie the mailman with love.

added.title: Reformed
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Garnet chase after a monster that's been loose in the Temple.

added.title: Sworn to the Sword
added.description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.

added.title: Rising Tides, Crashing Skies
added.description: Ronaldo does some investigative reporting on whether Steven and the Crystal Gems are safe for Beach City.

added.title: Keeping It Together
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems revisit the Kindergarten and find a dark secret.

added.title: We Need to Talk
added.description: Greg tells Steven and Connie the story of how he learned about Gem fusion.

added.title: Chille Tid
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems try to relax with a slumber party.

added.title: Cry for Help
added.description: Steven's favorite TV show gets interrupted by a magical disturbance.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: Onion Friend
added.description: Steven and Amethyst visit the strange world of Onion's house.

added.title: Historical Friction
added.description: Steven and Jamie put on a play about the founding of Beach City.

added.title: Friend Ship
added.description: The Crystal Gems explore an ancient Gem spaceship.

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: Homeworld Bound
added.description: Steven heads to the Diamonds for advice on how to control his new powers.

added.title: Everything's Fine
added.description: Steven insists that everything is fine.

added.title: I Am My Monster
added.description: Everything is not fine.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: Bonnibel Bubblegum
added.description: A long lost artifact causes Princess Bubblegum to harken back to the creation of the Candy Kingdom.

added.title: Gumbaldia
added.description: Finn and Jake, as ambassadors of the Candy Kingdom, travel to a powerful new city-state in a last ditch effort to stave off war.

added.title: Ketchup
added.description: BMO and Marceline swap stories about their recent adventures.

added.title: Fionna and Cake and Fionna
added.description: An unexpected critic shows up at Ice King's latest Fionna and Cake book reading.

added.title: Furniture & Meat
added.description: Big money problems send Finn and Jake to Wildberry Kingdom.

added.title: Princess Potluck
added.description: Ice King gets super jealous when he finds out that he wasn't invited to the Princess Potluck.

added.title: Candy Streets
added.description: Lumpy Space Princess is robbed and faints before she can tell Finn and Jake who robbed her.

added.title: Time Sandwich
added.description: Jake crafts the most delicious sandwich ever, but when Magic Man steals it, Finn must defy the laws of space and time to win back Jake's creation.

added.title: Red Starved
added.description: Finn, Jake and Marceline are trapped in an underground cavern with no red in sight. If Marceline doesn't feed, she will turn into a vampiric beast and suck out all of Jake's blood! Finn heads off to explore the cave and find something red to satiate her until they can be rescued.

added.title: Root Beer Guy
added.description: Root Beer Guy works a boring job during the day and tries to write mystery stories at night. But his life is about to change when he witnesses Finn and Jake kidnapping Princess Bubblegum!

added.title: Apple Wedding
added.description: You are cordially invited to the wedding of the year! But who will be united in matrimony?

added.title: Lemonhope
added.description: Tired of all of Princess Bubblegum's talk about responsibility, Lemonhope yearns for true freedom. So he sets off on the greatest adventure of his lemony life. Though Lemonhope finds refuge from the desert with monster hunter Phlannel Boxingday, he might not be able to escape the ghosts of his past.

added.title: Princess Cookie
added.description: Finn and Jake are called on to solve a Candy Kingdom hostage crisis when a rogue cookie takes over.

added.title: Thank You
added.description: The Snow Golem and his beseeching pup pay a visit to the Fire Kingdom.

added.title: The Other Tarts
added.description: Finn and Jake volunteer for a dangerous assignment: currying rare tarts for a meeting of Ooo royalty.

added.title: Donut Factory Holiday
added.description: The guys have to return a VHS copy of their favorite terrible movie or else pay a huge late fee.

added.title: The Thanksgiving Special
added.description: The park guys need to get Thanksgiving dinner for their families to save Thanksgiving.

added.title: Pie Contest
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to prove to Benson that they can be judges at the pie contest.

added.title: Sandwich of Death
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to find a cure for the Death Sandwich before Benson dies.

added.title: Limousine Lunchtime
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to clean Maellard's limo before he gets back from vacation.

added.title: Family BBQ
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a handshake from Margaret's dad.

added.title: Fortune Cookie
added.description: Rigby swaps fortune cookie fortunes with Benson.

added.title: Eggscellent
added.description: Mordecai wants to win a hat for Rigby.

added.title: The Best Burger in the World
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to finish their chores before they can have burgers.

added.title: Fancy Restaurant
added.description: Muscle Man has to impress his girlfriend's parents at a fancy dinner.

added.title: Sugar Rush
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to pick up the donuts for the morning meeting.

added.title: Peeps
added.description: Benson gets surveillance cameras to keep track of Mordecai and Rigby on the job.

added.title: This is My Jam
added.description: Rigby gets a terrible, terrible song stuck in his head and will go to any lengths to get it out.

added.title: Caffeinated Concert Tickets
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby make a deal with a Coffee Bean to help them stay awake to work major overtime to pay for concert tickets.

added.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby lie about being astronauts in order to cut in line at a restaurant.

added.title: A Very Special Blossom/Daylight Savings
added.description: A Very Special Blossom: When the Professor wants an expensive gift for Father's Day, Blossom makes the mistake of taking what she can't afford instead of giving him a gift from the heart./Daylight Savings: The Powerpuff Girls are exhausted in school from saving Townsville past their bedtime. What will happen to their town when the girls are put on a curfew?

added.title: Slave the Day/Los Dos Mojos
added.description: Slave The Day: The girls save Big Billy's life, and he is forever indebted. But how will they get this bumbling fellow out of their way so they can save the world?/Los Dos Mojos: After she gets knocked on the head, Bubbles wakes up thinking she is Mojo Jojo. What is the world going to do with two evil Mojos?

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever/Just Desserts
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever: It's raining in Townsville and there is no crime or villainy afoot. So the girls must stay inside and come up with their very own Powerpuff adventure./Just Desserts: The Smith Family is back and they want revenge. Harold, Maryanne and the kids become a super villain team and make it their goal to destroy the perfect Powerpuff family.

added.title: Imaginary Fiend/Cootie Gras
added.description: Imaginary Fiend: The new boy in school has a special friend nobody else can see. When this imaginary friend begins destroying the class, the girls must imagine how to stop him./Cootie Gras: Mojo observes that everyone is staying away from little Harry Pitt because he has cooties. So Mojo concocts a plan to keep the girls away by using this cootie-covered boy as bait.

added.title: Mo Job/Pet Feud
added.description: Mo Job: Princess hires Mojo to devise the perfect plan to destroy the girls, who are quite shocked when they find Princess has powers equal to their own./Pet Feud: The Professor creates the perfect little pet. But there's only one catch: he can only be fed once a day. When the girls each feed him, they find that their sweet little friend has become a wild beast!

added.title: Rebel Rebel
added.description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

added.title: Our Brand is Chaos
added.description: Bubbles and Buttercup make a deal without realizing the consequences.

added.title: Tagalong
added.description: Buttercup is tired of Bubbles following her everywhere.

added.title: Brainlord
added.description: A new superhero arrives in Townsville with a dark secret.

added.title: Checkin' Out!
added.description: A trip to the supermarket has bizarre consequences.

added.title: Drama Bomb
added.description: The school play goes off the rails when the drama teacher interferes.

added.title: Watch It!
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls are tasked with keeping a priceless gem safe from thieves.

added.title: Man Up 4: The Donnyest Game
added.description: With Man-Boy on the loose, Donny must be prepared for anything.

added.title: The Oct-Father
added.description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

added.title: Sideline Dad
added.description: When the Girls start playing soccer, the Professor goes overboard.

added.title: Escape from Monster Island
added.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

added.title: Princess Buttercup
added.description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

added.title: The Stayover
added.description: After going overboard on the candy, Blossom and Buttercup wake up with no memory of last night and no idea where Bubbles is! They must piece together the events of last night and find Bubbles before the Professor gets back!

added.title: Painbow
added.description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

added.title: Horn, Sweet Horn
added.description: Bubbles convinces the Professor to test his new transmogrifying ray on her new friend Donny the Pony in an effort to help him become the unicorn he's always wanted to be. But when it turns Donny into a monster instead, she must stop him before he destroys Townsville!

added.title: No Day Like Snow Day
added.description: When a blizzard hits the town, Master Frown tries to ruin everyone's fun by pretending to be a magical snowman! But when he gets frozen inside, Master Frown must worry less about ruining everyone's good time and instead not turning into a Frown-sicle, while he's forced to experience the joys of the holiday season!

added.title: Kaiju Kitty
added.description: When a giant monster attacks the Unikingdom, the gang fights back with Dr. Fox's awesome new secret weapon: a massive mega robot! But after the threat is contained, Unikitty doesn't want to stop using the  awesome robot, so she finds excuses for them to use it for everything, no matter how pointless. But what if the greatest threat to the kingdom turns out to be them?

added.title: Wishing Well
added.description: When Puppycorn uses a wishing well and it doesn't come true, Unikitty is shocked to discover the reason: all the wishes made over the years can't be granted because they're trapped at the bottom of the well (it's a dumb system.) She frees them to bring joy to the town… only to discover that they've gone a little bad after years trapped in a dark hole. Soon, they wish it would end!

added.title: Hide N' Seek
added.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: When Master Frown's head is stuck on Unikitty's butt, she vows to help him get his own body back, but first, she has to attend to her nice princess duties! But sharing a body with Master Frown can get pretty complicated, especially when Master Frown has his own agenda.

added.title: Pet Pet
added.description: Unikitty and the gang bring home a tiny creature they name Pet Pet, but Richard won't let them keep it if they can't prove they are responsible owners. But when Pet Pet runs away, Unikitty must pretend to be Pet Pet until they can find him, or Richard will never let them have Pet Pet (or any pet) ever again! Will Unikitty survive pet training, or finally admit responsibility is a lot harder than she thought?

added.title: Kitty Court
added.description: When Unikitty has a little auto incident with Master Frown, he insists on taking it to court! Frown's thrilled. There's nothing worse than boring old court and he can't wait to subject Unikitty to it! Unikitty is happy to make things right but the trial will be in Unikitty Court, which is so nonsensical and fun. It's Frown's worst nightmare! Will Master Frown succeed in bumming Unikitty out? Or will he be the one punished by their legal antics?

added.title: Lab Cat
added.description: Dr. Fox's robot helpers go on strike, so Unikitty and Puppycorn volunteer to be her lab rats, er, research assistants in a bold new experiment rocketing them into space! But as the mission grows more dangerous, Dr. Fox is forced to choose between the scientific breakthrough of her dreams and ever seeing her friends again!

added.title: The Zone
added.description: Unikitty keeps losing at video games to her little brother Puppycorn, so she acquires a super-powered video game controller from Dr. Fox to help. To her surprise, it actually controls other people, and the castle goes into lockdown like a real-world video game! At first it seems fun, but will she learn that life isn't a game?

added.title: Too Many Unikittys
added.description: Unikitty comes to the conclusion that everyone would be a lot happier if they would just think the way she does, and with Dr. Fox's help, maybe they can! Unikitty copies her brainwaves into all her friends and turns them Unikitty-fied, so everyone can always be positive! But soon Unikitty quickly realizes there can be too much of a good Princess!

added.title: Film Fest
added.description: It's opening night at the Unikingdom Film Festival! Everyone's excited to see what the friends made, particularly Richard, who considers himself the ultimate film expert and can't wait to blow everyone else's films out of the water with his own. But after playing the critic, will Rick's film be a masterpiece or a flop?

added.title: Unikitty News!
added.description: You're watching the Unikingdom News Show Super Good Morning Time Program Action Information Show, a variety news program put on (badly) by Unikitty and the gang: Hawkodile does the weather, Puppycorn does sports despite knowing none of the rules, Dr. Fox puts on a fun science-y cooking segment that goes awry, and Richard wants this to stop. Unikitty's got some hard hitting reporting and a big scoop after the break, if the studio survives that long!

added.title: Dinner Apart-y
added.description: Unikitty and Puppycorn are invited to Master Frown and Brock's apartment for a dinner party. But the two roommates are butting heads, and are anything but on the same page. Can Unikitty help Brock and Master Frown get back in harmony before the dinner party is ruined? Will Puppycorn figure out which door is the bathroom?

added.title: R & Arr
added.description: It's Lazy Sunday, and Unikitty and Puppycorn are having such an amazing time hanging out on the couch, they never want to move! Richard insists they have chores to do, but they're unwilling to let Lazy Sunday end. The two go to ridiculous lengths to never leave the comfort of their sofa, rowing it across the castle and like a ship and conscripting their friends to abandon their chores and join Lazy Sunday… no matter how dangerous and impossible it might become!

added.title: License to Punch
added.description: Hawkodile's caught by the Action Police for bodyguarding without an Action License. He's can't protect the kingdom or do anything rad until he does, but the test at the DMV (The Department of Mayhem and Violence) is for nerds! Forced to retire his gloves, Hawkodile struggles to live a life without punching, so Unikitty vows to help her friend contain his urge to be action-y and study for the test. But there's more to the test than meets the eye.

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Pizza Hero
added.description: It's the end of the school year, and as is tradition at Aberdale Elementary, Papa Marianio is slated to dish out his famous pizza along with a spectacle of song and dance. As the kids wait in excitement, they share memories about times with Papa.

added.title: The Interrogation
added.description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Lost in the Supermarket
added.description: During a trip to the supermarket with his mom, Clarence discovers produce adventure and coupon intrigue in aisle five...and every other aisle.

added.title: Dinner Party
added.description: When Clarence's mom takes Clarence to a stuffy dinner party, Clarence embarks on a quest for fun wherever it can be found.

added.title: Zoo
added.description: Clarence and Belson make a true odd couple when they're paired up during a field trip to the zoo and find themselves locked inside after hours.

added.title: Rise and Shine
added.description: A glimpse at the wild, secret adventures Clarence undertakes each day before the rest of us, and the sun, get up.

added.title: Man of the House
added.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

added.title: Puddle Eyes
added.description: A nap in mud seals Clarence's eyes and leaves him sightless, potentially dooming his team's chances in the school's ill-conceived "Vision Bee."

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: Neighborhood Grill
added.description: Clarence is so troubled by the sight of his teacher in a social setting outside of school, he can't stop himself from intruding on her doomed blind date.

added.title: Goose Chase
added.description: While at the park, Clarence happily feeds some birds his sandwich, imagining himself as their king. He has a great time until one persistent goose will not leave him alone!

added.title: Goldfish Follies
added.description: Clarence buys a goldfish, but when the goldfish bag breaks before he can get home, Clarence must keep his new friend out of harms way and get him back into water before it's too late.

added.title: The Big Petey Pizza Problem
added.description: Jeff has everything in place for his birthday at Papa Petey's Pins and Pies but Gilben is also having his party there, stealing Jeff's thunder. Jeff gets even more upset when the kids suggest they merge their parities for a double birthday. Can Jeff learn to roll with the punches and share his special day?

added.title: The Cake Mistake
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus eat a cake meant for someone else.

added.title: Pizza Steve's Past
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang learn of Pizza Steve's past stint in the food service industry. Pizza Steve wasn't always the Pizza Steve they know and love.

added.title: Full Grown Pizza
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes it hard for Pizza Steve to prove he's not a baby.

added.title: Lil' Mac
added.description: Mr. Gus' nephew terrorizes Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve.

added.title: Pizza Eve
added.description: Uncle Grandpa falls for Pizza Steve's "girlfriend" and ends up in serious danger.

added.title: Taco Comet
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang go undercover to taste the most sought after treat in the cosmos: the Taco Comet.

added.title: The Great Spaghetti Western
added.description: Mr. Gus repeatedly runs afoul of a crooked mayor while winning the hears of the townsfolk.

added.title: Watermelon Gag
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets a watermelon stuck in his mouth, he is unable to ask for help and people interpret it as a comedy routine. As Uncle Grandpa's popularity rises, his friendships and morale suffer.

added.title: Nacho Cheese
added.description: Pizza Steve's father comes to visit the gang and almost immediately gets on their nerves with his over the top antics. Pizza Steve must get rid of his dad, and prove to himself that he doesn't need to live in his father's shadow any longer.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Ate My Homework
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa shows up and mistakenly eats a kid's Egyptian diorama for school, he helps the kid bring an actual pyramid to class, but accidentally unleashes an evil mummy on the world.

added.title: Charlie Burgers
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and crew help a friendly dog, Charlie Burgers, find his lost ball by literally turning the world upside down.

added.title: Future Pizza
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa travels back through time with a warning that Pizza Steve will do something to offend him in the next five minutes, Pizza Steve begins to obsess over what he could possibly do to offend Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: Greed causes Pizza Steve's latest business venture to backfire.

added.title: Pizza Steve's Diary
added.description: When his diary winds up in the hands of Mr. Gus, Pizza Steve goes to great lengths to get it back before Mr. Gus can read all of his deepest, darkest secrets.

added.title: Misfortune Cookie
added.description: After receiving an ominous fortune, Uncle Grandpa must snoop out whom among his friends is an enemy in disguise.

added.title: Bedtime Routine
added.description: Jessica wants to be a big kid and get ready for bed all on her own, but she can't remember everything in her routine.

added.title: Small Uncle's Big Bath
added.description: When Jessica discovers her favorite toy is dirty she volunteers to give him a bath.

added.title: The Big Kid Playground
added.description: Jessica goes in the big kid part of the playground for the first time, and befriends Stanleigh.

added.title: Grocery Store Friend
added.description: While helping Duane at the supermarket, Jessica meets a new friend and has trouble staying focused on her responsibilities.

added.title: Glow Toy
added.description: When Jessica can't get a new toy to work, she learns a new way to appreciate it.

added.title: Jessica's Restaurant
added.description: Jessica opens a restaurant with her good friend Stanleigh, but will they be able to keep their customers happy?

added.title: Little Twin
added.description: When Jessica meets another kid at the park with an identical look as her, the two quickly form an unbreakable bond.

added.title: Spike the Hedgehog
added.description: When Jessica pet sits Stanleigh's hedgehog, she has to think on her feet.

added.title: Sleepover
added.description: Jessica has a sleepover at her grandparents' house and must survive the night without her plush toy, Small Uncle.

added.title: Family Photo
added.description: When the family has to dress up for a family photo, Jessica decides to express herself.

added.title: Drawing Time
added.description: When the tv goes out, Jessica and her friends make up their own story to entertain themselves.

added.title: Jessica's Picnic
added.description: Jessica and Nicole set out to have a fun picnic but run into challenges when everything goes wrong.

added.title: The Secret Invention
added.description: Jessica finds out Craig is working on a Secret Invention and sets out to help him with it.

added.title: Big Kid Bike
added.description: Jessica wants to learn to ride a big kid bike.

added.title: Rain Rescue
added.description: Jessica rescues her toys from the backyard as rain approaches.

removed.title: The Haunted Dollhouse
removed.description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

removed.title: Viral Spiral
removed.description: When the Amoeba Boys wreak havoc on the internet, Bubbles has to hack her sisters in to stop them.

removed.title: Tiara Trouble
removed.description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

removed.title: The Legend of the Library
removed.description: When the library is thrown into disarray, an ancient ghost is awoken.

removed.title: The Wrinklegruff Gals
removed.description: Sick of being the tiniest kids at their new school, the girls convince Professor Utonium to create a potion to make them older! Unfortunately, when they take too much, they become senior citizens and a prime target for Mojo Jojo!

removed.title: Trick or Creek
removed.description: It's Halloween at the Creek, and Craig is on a mission to collect as much candy as humanly possible, but a spooky ghoul from the Creek's past threatens his haul.
